						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Māṟavarman</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Tribhº Emmaṇḍº Kulaśēkharadēva: (Acc. 1268 A.D.) = Year lost.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged and obliterated.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of a <hi rend="italic">nandā</hi> lamp to the temple of the god Bagavatīśvaramuḍaiyār of Śuttavalli <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vīravinōdach-chaturvvēdimaṅgalam in Mēl-Vēmba-nāḍu by a certain Veḷḷaikkūttaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Periyapperumāḷ. It is stated that the gift was accepted by the <hi rend="italic">Śivabrāhamaṇas</hi> of the 30 circles attached to the temple. Other details are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
